=begin

The four adjacent digits in the 1000-digit number that have the 
greatest product are 9 × 9 × 8 × 9 = 5832.
Find the thirteen adjacent digits in the 1000-digit number that
have the greatest product. What is the value of this product?

=end


def largestproduct
    # a more efficient way is o detect zeros and skip the 12 characters before and after when calculating products
    #perhapskeep an array of all beginning indexes from whic a sequence of length 13 whic no zeros appear starts?
    #or even more efficient, delete the 12 digies before and after every zero, making the number a lot smaller
    #calc the sum of the numbers in that index. if the sum is bigger, then so is the product?
    
    greatestproduct = 0
    startindex = 0
    num = 
    num = num.to_s
    i = 0
    
    while i <= num.length-13
         temp = num[i].to_i*num[i+1].to_i*num[i+2].to_i*num[i+3].to_i*num[i+4].to_i*num[i+5].to_i*num[i+6].to_i*num[i+7].to_i*num[i+8].to_i*num[i+9].to_i*num[i+10].to_i*num[i+11].to_i*num[i+12].to_i
        if temp > greatestproduct
            greatestproduct = temp
            startindex = i
        end
        i +=1 
    end
    
    return greatestproduct

end


puts largestproduct
